how to make very simple cookies its night i'm bored and alone no one to talk on msn and i'm out of bread so i have chocolate cream with me and its too sweet so i wanna make some simple cookies but i dont know how so recipes please simple sugar cookies ingredients cup butter no substitutes softened cups confectioners' sugar egg teaspoon vanilla extract cups all purpose flour teaspoon baking soda teaspoon cream of tartar teaspoon salt directions in a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar beat in egg and vanilla combine the flour baking soda cream of tartar and salt gradually add to the creamed mixture shape into two in rolls wrap in plastic wrap refrigerate for hour or until firm unwrap cut into in slices place in apart on ungreased baking sheets bake at degrees f for minutes remove to wire racks to cool rocky road ingredients cups semisweet chocolate chips cup peanut butter cups miniature marshmallows directions grease a x inch pan heat chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat in a medium saucepan until chips are completely melted remove from heat stir in marshmallows pour into prepared pan cool can be put into refrigerator to cool cut and enjoy no bake fudge cookies ingredients cups white sugar cup milk cup butter cup peanut butter cups quick cooking oats tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder teaspoon vanilla extract cup raisins directions in a large saucepan combine cups sugar cup milk cup butter and boil for minute take off heat and add peanut butter quick cooking oats cocoa vanilla and raisins stir well drop by teaspoon on wax paper let sit one hour Bagel Dairy Vinegar Chili con carne Cuisine of Denmark Cuisine of the Philippines Confectionery Bacon Chocolate Salty Balls Oreo Cuisine of Brazil Mayonnaise Biscuit Twix Kit Kat Peanut butter Butter Porridge Brewery Flour Sugar Maple syrup Cocoa Puff pastry Cooking Tortilla Pizza D__ner kebab Turkish Delight Barbecue Plastic Horehound Turkish coffee Peruvian cuisine Muffin Sandwich Milk Hot dog Baked Alaska Ramen 